fix: use WidgetProvider theme colors across all components

BREAKING CHANGE: Spinner converted from class to functional component.

All components were importing the static THEME_COLORS constant
from helper/index.ts. This constant is evaluated once at module
load time, so custom colors from WidgetProvider were ignored.

Components now call useRnWidgetContext('colors') at render time
to read merged theme colors from the provider context.

Files changed:
- TextField.tsx: focus/error borders use context colors
- Button.tsx: default wrapperStyle uses context primary
- Empty.tsx: ActivityIndicator uses context primary
- Select.tsx: selected option border uses context orange
- SelectInput.js: error border and icon use context colors
- Spinner.tsx: converted to functional component with hook
- Touch.tsx: loading indicator uses context primary
- View.tsx: gradient defaults use context primary/secondary
- styles.view.ts: style param accepts StyleProp<ViewStyle>

Version bumped to 0.2.1 and published to npm.
